 &lt;p&gt;⭐️⭐️⭐️&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://leetcode.com/problems/reveal-cards-in-increasing-order/description/?envType=daily-question&amp;amp;envId=2024-04-10&#34;&gt;&lt;ins class=&#34;dot&#34;&gt;題目敘述&lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are given an integer array  &lt;code&gt;deck&lt;/code&gt; . There is a deck of cards where every card has a unique integer. The integer on the  &lt;code&gt;ith&lt;/code&gt;  card is  &lt;code&gt;deck[i]&lt;/code&gt; .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can order the deck in any order you want. Initially, all the cards start face down (unrevealed) in one deck.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will do the following steps repeatedly until all cards are revealed:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take the top card of the deck, reveal it, and take it out of the deck.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If there are still cards in the deck then put the next top card of the deck at the bottom of the deck.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If there are still unrevealed cards, go back to step 1. Otherwise, stop.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Return &lt;em&gt;an ordering of the deck that would reveal the cards in increasing order.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note&lt;/strong&gt; that the first entry in the answer is considered to be the top of the deck.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-1&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-1&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 1&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; deck = [17,13,11,2,3,5,7]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; [2,13,3,11,5,17,7]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Explanation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
We get the deck in the order [17,13,11,2,3,5,7] (this order does not matter), and reorder it.&lt;br /&gt;
After reordering, the deck starts as [2,13,3,11,5,17,7], where 2 is the top of the deck.&lt;br /&gt;
We reveal 2, and move 13 to the bottom.  The deck is now [3,11,5,17,7,13].&lt;br /&gt;
We reveal 3, and move 11 to the bottom.  The deck is now [5,17,7,13,11].&lt;br /&gt;
We reveal 5, and move 17 to the bottom.  The deck is now [7,13,11,17].&lt;br /&gt;
We reveal 7, and move 13 to the bottom.  The deck is now [11,17,13].&lt;br /&gt;
We reveal 11, and move 17 to the bottom.  The deck is now [13,17].&lt;br /&gt;
We reveal 13, and move 17 to the bottom.  The deck is now [17].&lt;br /&gt;
We reveal 17.&lt;br /&gt;
Since all the cards revealed are in increasing order, the answer is correct.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-2&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-2&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 2&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; deck = [1,1000]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; [1,1000]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;解題思路&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#解題思路&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; 解題思路&lt;/h2&gt;
