 &lt;p&gt;⭐️⭐️⭐️&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://leetcode.com/problems/remove-zero-sum-consecutive-nodes-from-linked-list/description/?envType=daily-question&amp;amp;envId=2024-03-12&#34;&gt;&lt;ins class=&#34;dot&#34;&gt;題目敘述&lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Given the  &lt;code&gt;head&lt;/code&gt;  of a linked list, we repeatedly delete consecutive sequences of nodes that sum to  &lt;code&gt;0&lt;/code&gt;  until there are no such sequences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After doing so, return the head of the final linked list.  You may return any such answer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(Note that in the examples below, all sequences are serializations of  &lt;code&gt;ListNode&lt;/code&gt;  objects.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-1&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-1&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 1&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; head = [1,2,-3,3,1]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; [3,1]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt; The answer [1,2,1] would also be accepted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-2&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-2&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 2&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; head = [1,2,3,-3,4]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; [1,2,4]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-3&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-3&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 3&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; head = [1,2,3,-3,-2]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; [1]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;note info no-icon&#34;&gt;
